Announcement
The
Schedule/Contact Information/Requirements has been updated! (2011/6/24)
    
Course Information and Syllabus
This course consists of a series of speeches given by researchers/scholars in the general field of Information Technology and Management. Its purpose is to expose the students to current topics and issues in the subject field. Each talk will be about 90 minutes long, followed by a 10 to 20 minutes discussion session.
  



Chairs



Seng-Cho Chou  (曹承礎) 
      

Office:
  Room 810, Building II, 
  College of Management. 
  Email: chou ( AT )
  ntu.edu.tw
  Tel: 3366-1182





Yih-Kuen Tsay  (蔡益坤) 
      

Office:
  Room 1108, Building II, 
  College of Management.
Email: tsay ( AT ) im.ntu.edu.tw
  Tel: 3366-1189









Requirements
Students are required to 
(a) attend  all talks except two of their choice and 
(b) submit  reviews (1-2 pages) for 8 talks also of their choice.

Each  review of a talk is due at the beginning of the next class meeting following  the talk. Please use A4 (or similar  size) paper. Late submissions will NOT be accepted. Plagiarism is a  serious violation and may result in failing the course and/or being reported to  the University.

Grading
Attendance 40%, Discussion Participation 20%, Reviews 40%





